The paper deals with crop mapping using machine learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of time-series data and the warping of angular distances, which could be related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with geographical areas and farming practices, which could be related to graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
